docs.abstract: Margrethe Vestager, whose billion-dollar fines have made her loathed by Silicon Valley, has won new powers that give her unrivaled regulatory reach. President Trump says she “hates the United States.”
docs.snippet: Margrethe Vestager, whose billion-dollar fines have made her loathed by Silicon Valley, has won new powers that give her unrivaled regulatory reach. President Trump says she “hates the United States.”
docs.lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — For five years, Margrethe Vestager was the scourge of Silicon Valley, levying billions of dollars in fines and initiating investigations against Google, Apple and Facebook for violating antitrust laws and harming consumers.

headline.main: E.U.’s New Digital Czar: ‘Most Powerful Regulator of Big Tech on the Planet’
headline.print_headline: E.U.’s New Digital Czar Expands Her Portfolio

docs.abstract: The live-streaming platform, owned by Amazon, has more viewers than many cable channels. But a new ad campaign aims to show it’s good for more than video games.
docs.snippet: The live-streaming platform, owned by Amazon, has more viewers than many cable channels. But a new ad campaign aims to show it’s good for more than video games.
docs.lead_paragraph: Without video games, Twitch would not be what it is now: a live-streaming platform with millions of devoted viewers and broadcasters, some of them with tattoos of the company’s logo. But the company, which Amazon bought five years ago for more than $1 billion, has ambitions beyond serving fans of Fortnite and World of Warcraft.

headline.main: Twitch Users Watch Billions of Hours of Video, but the Site Wants to Go Beyond Fortnite
headline.print_headline: Twitch Aims To Play More Than Games

docs.abstract: A sweeping Times investigation of all President Trump's tweets and followers shows how he has transformed the platform into a vital, and perilous, instrument of power.
docs.snippet: A sweeping Times investigation of all President Trump's tweets and followers shows how he has transformed the platform into a vital, and perilous, instrument of power.
docs.lead_paragraph: Donald J. Trump has exploited social media like no other American president, using it as a springboard to change policy, as a cudgel against critics and as an outlet for self-affirmation. “He needs to tweet like we need to eat,” said Kellyanne Conway, his White House counselor.

docs.abstract: The Emmy-winning TV creator talks about his return to television with “The Romanoffs” and addresses a harassment allegation.
docs.snippet: The Emmy-winning TV creator talks about his return to television with “The Romanoffs” and addresses a harassment allegation.
docs.lead_paragraph: Los Angeles — Before writing an episode of his new Amazon series “The Romanoffs,” Matthew Weiner would ring a small bell. The trinket was a Christmas gift from one of the writers on the show, and the sound it made was essential for “clearing the air,” Mr. Weiner said. “It was a moment of faith in intuition and the process.”

headline.main: Matthew Weiner on Life After ‘Mad Men,’ Sexual Harassment and His New Amazon Show
headline.print_headline: After ‘Mad Men,’ an Idea That Spans the Globe

docs.abstract: After poor box-office numbers for Mindy Kaling’s “Late Night,” the company shrank its ambitious release plan for a big fall movie, “The Aeronauts.”
docs.snippet: After poor box-office numbers for Mindy Kaling’s “Late Night,” the company shrank its ambitious release plan for a big fall movie, “The Aeronauts.”
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — “The Aeronauts,” an adventure film about swashbuckling 19th-century hot-air balloonists, was built for the big screen. Led by an Oscar winner, Eddie Redmayne, and a “Star Wars” star, Felicity Jones, it has real cinematic sweep, with sequences that take place miles above sea level. In May, Amazon Studios announced that the movie would play exclusively on IMAX screens for a one-week engagement before “a full theatrical run.”

headline.main: Behind Amazon’s Sudden Change in Its Film Strategy
headline.print_headline: Amazon Downsizes Its Ambitions For Cinema

docs.abstract: The E.U.’s top antitrust regulator ordered Broadcom to halt specific practices while the bloc investigates possible anticompetitive activity.

docs.lead_paragraph: European authorities took an even more aggressive approach than usual to regulating the technology industry Wednesday when they applied a rarely used rule, ordering a company to halt a potentially anticompetitive practice while an investigation is underway.

headline.main: Europe’s Margrethe Vestager Takes a Rare Step Toward Big Tech
headline.print_headline: E.U. Regulator Will Rein In Broadcom During Antitrust Inquiry
